name: Mystic collage #1
description: From the hand of my sisters I found prayer, humility and gratitude and between songs, giggles, tears and drums we raise a prayer to our beauty and our power. then, From the bowels of the earth we are reborn: From the mud and the very belly of the pacha mama we let go of all ties to find ourselves ONE with everything. (I've been here before!) (I've already been here!) the memories returned ... That was me, but I was not just me: there was no mask, nothing to hide or hide. our wound was the same, our mask was the same! as well as our light, our love and together with the heat, we find ourselves being one, not only among ourselves but with each cell and manifestation of life. Being a single heart beating in the matrix of earth. and we remember: I was already here sister! and I was here with you !! I love you sister!! we were born !!!
